# acme.sh + Mythic Beasts DNS-01 Environment Template
# Copy to .env.acme and fill in real values before issuing certs.
# .env.acme is listed explicitly in .gitignore (alongside the other
# .env.<service> files); the real file never lands in git.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Mythic Beasts Primary API v2 credentials
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Create an account-level API key in the Mythic Beasts control panel
# under "Account → API keys". This is the OAuth2 key used by acme.sh's
# `dnsapi/dns_mythic_beasts.sh` hook (NOT the older per-domain "DNS API
# key", which is a different, legacy credential type).
#
# Restrict the key's permissions so it can write ONLY TXT records named
# `_acme-challenge` on the `digitalbadges.scot` zone - this keeps the
# blast radius of a leaked secret as small as the DNS-01 protocol allows.
#
# The env var names MB_AK / MB_AS are literally what the acme.sh hook
# reads from the environment - do not rename.
MB_AK=""    # API key ID emitted by the control panel
MB_AS=""    # API secret emitted by the control panel

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Let's Encrypt account email - used for expiry notifications.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
LE_EMAIL=""

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SAN list for the wildcard cert. Edit if you ever add a new apex.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ACME_DOMAIN_LIST="-d digitalbadges.scot -d *.digitalbadges.scot"
